sentences: David Friesen (born May 6, 1942 in Tacoma, Washington) is an American jazz bassist.
He played with John Handy and Marian McPartland and following this, with Joe Henderson; in 1975, he toured in Europe with Billy Harper.
His first album as a session leader appeared that year.
In 1976, he began collaborating with guitarist John Stowell; the pair would work together often.
He appeared with Ted Curson at the Monterey Jazz Festival in 1977.
His 1989 album Other Times, Other Places reached No. 11 on the U.S. Billboard Top Jazz Albums chart.
Textures (2014; with Christian Hassenstein, Joost Lijbaart)
